1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,100
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,075 --> 00:00:40,545
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:43,685 --> 00:00:44,685
Really?

5
00:00:45,085 --> 00:00:46,385
You'll meet her soon.

6
00:00:47,715 --> 00:00:48,985
It wasn't that I was being insensitive.

7
00:00:49,785 --> 00:00:51,185
It was just that instead of
a small gift like a cake,

8
00:00:51,185 --> 00:00:53,725
I wanted to do something
so much better for you.

9
00:00:57,065 --> 00:00:58,095
To me...

10
00:00:59,235 --> 00:01:00,695
you're not a little kid anymore.

11
00:01:03,505 --> 00:01:04,805
And at some point,

12
00:01:06,735 --> 00:01:08,635
I started to see you in a different light.

13
00:01:12,175 --> 00:01:13,475
It wasn't that I was being insensitive.

14
00:01:14,215 --> 00:01:15,615
It was just that instead of
a small gift like a cake,

15
00:01:15,615 --> 00:01:18,215
I wanted to do something
so much better for you.

16
00:01:19,915 --> 00:01:20,955
To me,

17
00:01:21,785 --> 00:01:23,355
you're truly my number one priority.

18
00:01:23,355 --> 00:01:24,485
Without a doubt.

19
00:01:26,625 --> 00:01:27,625
Even more than my brother.

20
00:01:28,295 --> 00:01:31,065
He has plenty of close friends anyway.

21
00:01:33,165 --> 00:01:36,505
And I may be exaggerating a bit,
but with no strings attached,

22
00:01:37,365 --> 00:01:39,835
I want to be the one person
you can comfortably lean on...

23
00:01:40,435 --> 00:01:41,535
and rely on.

24
00:01:42,945 --> 00:01:44,105
I can be your big brother,

25
00:01:45,745 --> 00:01:47,715
or a father figure if you need one,

26
00:01:47,715 --> 00:01:48,715
emotionally.

27
00:01:49,245 --> 00:01:51,115
And sometimes a friend
you can really talk to.

28
00:01:51,645 --> 00:01:52,655
Anyway.

29
00:01:58,625 --> 00:02:00,095
To him, I'm...

30
00:02:00,155 --> 00:02:01,925
(To him, I'm...)

31
00:02:02,265 --> 00:02:04,425
I've definitely become happier
since I met you.

32
00:02:05,565 --> 00:02:07,835
And I feel more emotionally stable, too.

33
00:02:12,775 --> 00:02:13,775
Thank you.

34
00:02:14,375 --> 00:02:15,605
You don't have to thank me.

35
00:02:17,245 --> 00:02:20,475
From now on, if there's anything
you want or need...

36
00:02:21,145 --> 00:02:22,285
Don't I...

37
00:02:23,215 --> 00:02:24,815
make your heart flutter at all?

38
00:02:27,155 --> 00:02:29,355
Am I really just
like a little sister to you?

39
00:02:31,685 --> 00:02:33,295
Go ahead and hit this clueless guy.

40
00:02:38,995 --> 00:02:41,195
When I get focused on one thing,
I have a one-track mind.

41
00:02:45,205 --> 00:02:46,205
Are you cold?

42
00:02:48,535 --> 00:02:49,875
Let's dig in.

43
00:02:58,215 --> 00:02:59,215
What do you think?

44
00:03:00,555 --> 00:03:04,085
- It's good.
- Ambiance is a big part of it.

45
00:03:09,725 --> 00:03:10,865
What did you have for dinner?

46
00:03:11,495 --> 00:03:14,695
- A salmon salad around five.
- You must be starving, then.

47
00:03:14,895 --> 00:03:15,905
No.

48
00:03:19,235 --> 00:03:20,905
Why the short answers all of a sudden?

49
00:03:23,705 --> 00:03:24,775
I'm busy eating.

50
00:03:26,145 --> 00:03:27,375
You're so cute.

51
00:03:27,715 --> 00:03:30,245
- Only for you.
- You'd better be.

52
00:03:31,785 --> 00:03:34,455
Seeing you, I get why dads dote
on their daughters.

53
00:03:36,325 --> 00:03:38,355
You'll meet a good guy
and get married someday.

54
00:03:40,095 --> 00:03:41,725
But it'll be hard to find one
as great as me.

55
00:03:43,825 --> 00:03:45,025
Where's all this confidence coming from?

56
00:03:45,465 --> 00:03:48,095
Other than my education,
I'm pretty much the whole package, right?

57
00:03:51,935 --> 00:03:54,405
Shoot, I forgot the water again.

58
00:03:54,605 --> 00:03:56,705
- I'm not thirsty.
- You'll get an upset stomach.

59
00:04:05,315 --> 00:04:08,185
If you could just be mine
and stay by my side,

60
00:04:09,085 --> 00:04:10,285
I thought I could live on...

61
00:04:11,225 --> 00:04:14,155
without ever seeing my mom and dad again.

62
00:04:28,435 --> 00:04:30,105
(Ba Ra)

63
00:04:30,305 --> 00:04:33,345
(Ba Ra)

64
00:04:34,415 --> 00:04:38,615
(Geum Ba Ra)

65
00:04:39,455 --> 00:04:42,555
(Ba Ra)

66
00:04:42,625 --> 00:04:43,825
(Save)

67
00:04:49,595 --> 00:04:51,795
So you don't even like
Shine Muscat grapes?

68
00:04:51,965 --> 00:04:55,295
Yes. It's not tangy or anything.
It's just sweet.

69
00:04:55,365 --> 00:04:56,565
If I were a flavor, what would I be?

70
00:04:57,305 --> 00:04:58,905
Sweet? Tangy?

71
00:04:59,235 --> 00:05:00,235
Unripe.

72
00:05:02,075 --> 00:05:03,675
Compare me to an animal, then.

73
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:05,245
The lord of all creation.

74
00:05:05,945 --> 00:05:07,545
No animal comes to mind.

75
00:05:09,685 --> 00:05:11,245
You don't have to be nice.

76
00:05:11,815 --> 00:05:12,885
I'm serious.

77
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,555
I just take and take
from you, shamelessly.

78
00:05:16,525 --> 00:05:18,285
I want to give something back,

79
00:05:19,695 --> 00:05:21,125
but you already have everything.

80
00:05:22,295 --> 00:05:25,265
That's how love works.
It flows downward, not up.

81
00:05:26,295 --> 00:05:28,535
But plenty of children are devoted
to their parents.

82
00:05:29,005 --> 00:05:30,365
I guess I should have kids, right?

83
00:05:31,505 --> 00:05:33,235
That's the one thing I envy Ju Shin for.

84
00:05:35,435 --> 00:05:37,375
I'm so envious of Momo.

85
00:05:39,745 --> 00:05:41,045
The wind is chilly.

86
00:05:44,885 --> 00:05:48,085
It's still warm under the sand.
We came for a sand bath, remember?

87
00:05:50,325 --> 00:05:51,325
Don't you want to?

88
00:05:53,025 --> 00:05:54,625
We can wash up at the hotel.

89
00:05:54,625 --> 00:05:56,565
They sell golf wear in the lobby.

90
00:06:14,775 --> 00:06:15,785
Isn't it warm?

91
00:06:16,315 --> 00:06:17,385
It's fine.

92
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:18,645
How does it feel?

93
00:06:18,785 --> 00:06:21,715
It's a strange feeling.
But not in a bad way.

94
00:06:25,685 --> 00:06:27,425
You can really see the stars out here,
can't you?

95
00:06:27,995 --> 00:06:29,025
Yes.

96
00:06:29,965 --> 00:06:31,895
This is better than doing it
in the blazing sun.

97
00:06:32,195 --> 00:06:33,765
Who used to bury you in the sand?

98
00:06:34,535 --> 00:06:35,535
Your mom?

99
00:06:36,435 --> 00:06:37,435
My brother.

100
00:06:38,835 --> 00:06:40,835
He has such a great personality.

101
00:06:41,675 --> 00:06:44,105
I'm sure he has his own pain, deep down.

102
00:06:45,275 --> 00:06:46,915
But he never shows it. Not at all.

103
00:06:47,375 --> 00:06:49,445
You should try to have a deep talk
with him sometime.

104
00:06:50,985 --> 00:06:52,315
I've tried asking him,

105
00:06:53,885 --> 00:06:56,955
and he just said he's grateful
to be part of our family.

106
00:06:58,185 --> 00:06:59,195
End of story.

107
00:06:59,755 --> 00:07:01,555
You know how guys are bad
at expressing themselves.

108
00:07:01,995 --> 00:07:04,325
Me too. I'm so glad I met you.

109
00:07:04,795 --> 00:07:05,835
The feeling's mutual.

110
00:07:07,365 --> 00:07:09,665
I was always jealous of my friends
who had little sisters.

111
00:07:15,075 --> 00:07:16,075
This is weird.

112
00:07:17,345 --> 00:07:18,345
I'm getting sleepy.

113
00:07:19,975 --> 00:07:21,315
You're probably just tired.

114
00:07:21,645 --> 00:07:24,515
You drove for hours and even took a plane.

115
00:07:24,785 --> 00:07:26,885
You're not going to disappear
when I wake up, are you?

116
00:07:28,385 --> 00:07:29,585
Maybe.

117
00:07:33,125 --> 00:07:34,125
Give me your hand.

118
00:07:41,835 --> 00:07:44,765
How do you like a sand bath
under the moonlight?

119
00:07:47,175 --> 00:07:49,245
The one person who creates
these memories for me...

120
00:07:50,205 --> 00:07:51,375
is you.

121
00:07:52,475 --> 00:07:53,645
All your difficult memories...

122
00:07:55,045 --> 00:07:56,885
will be buried under good ones.

123
00:07:58,185 --> 00:07:59,815
I'll make sure of it.

124
00:08:01,455 --> 00:08:03,355
They don't make them like me anymore.

125
00:08:05,325 --> 00:08:06,325
That's true.

126
00:08:07,095 --> 00:08:08,525
You're really one of a kind.

127
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:10,325
I'm going to poke you in your side
from now on.

128
00:08:10,395 --> 00:08:11,965
But I'm really ticklish.

129
00:08:15,295 --> 00:08:16,935
I'm not good at expressing myself either.

130
00:08:18,205 --> 00:08:19,375
Because I grew up in the orphange,

131
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:21,335
I can't help
but be a bit emotionally withdrawn.

132
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:23,375
I admit it.

133
00:08:25,075 --> 00:08:26,275
I don't see that at all.

134
00:08:27,815 --> 00:08:28,875
I just think you're cute.

135
00:08:31,315 --> 00:08:32,385
And adorable.

136
00:08:35,585 --> 00:08:37,155
Aren't you curious about
what my name means?

137
00:08:38,155 --> 00:08:39,425
A lot of people ask me.

138
00:08:39,695 --> 00:08:41,655
You said it's "Jung Yoong" in reverse.

139
00:08:42,095 --> 00:08:44,565
- When did I tell you that?
- I heard it from An Hee.

140
00:08:44,925 --> 00:08:47,695
You must've heard that
when you were little. You remember?

141
00:08:48,165 --> 00:08:49,935
- Yes.
- Smarty-pants.

142
00:08:51,635 --> 00:08:53,035
He didn't talk trash about me, did he?

143
00:08:53,835 --> 00:08:54,875
Of course he did.

144
00:08:55,205 --> 00:08:57,305
So that's where
all my cringey stories came from.

145
00:08:57,775 --> 00:08:58,975
He said you were the most loyal person,

146
00:08:59,715 --> 00:09:02,215
and that Ha Yong Joong
was an incredible guy.

147
00:09:03,545 --> 00:09:05,515
When it comes to loyalty,
An Hee's the real deal.

148
00:09:08,355 --> 00:09:09,985
I was so busy developing my game...

149
00:09:11,355 --> 00:09:13,125
that I couldn't find you sooner.

150
00:09:15,025 --> 00:09:16,265
Yong Joong,

151
00:09:18,565 --> 00:09:23,035
did you ever believe that when people die,
they become a star?

152
00:09:23,505 --> 00:09:24,505
No.

153
00:09:25,975 --> 00:09:28,905
I have to take care of my kiddo
for An Hee's sake too.

154
00:09:34,515 --> 00:09:35,845
Look for the Big Dipper.

155
00:09:36,585 --> 00:09:37,585
Okay.

156
00:09:40,985 --> 00:09:41,985
There it is.

157
00:09:53,165 --> 00:09:57,165
I wish I could fall asleep
just like this and never wake up.

158
00:09:59,135 --> 00:10:01,175
All my hope is completely gone.

159
00:10:02,745 --> 00:10:04,805
I wanted a baby more than anything.

160
00:10:06,175 --> 00:10:09,545
A beautiful baby that looks just like you,
not anyone else.

161
00:10:11,645 --> 00:10:13,785
I have nothing to live for now.

162
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,385
Just thinking of you...

163
00:10:20,795 --> 00:10:22,625
was enough to get me through anything.

164
00:10:46,715 --> 00:10:48,685
We're not even blood-related.

165
00:10:50,585 --> 00:10:52,725
Is that all I am to you?
Just a little sister?

166
00:10:55,225 --> 00:10:57,065
If I were to disappear from this world,

167
00:10:58,825 --> 00:11:01,095
I wonder if you'd think of me
as a woman then?

168
00:11:03,135 --> 00:11:05,265
Not as that little girl with the bob cut,

169
00:11:06,475 --> 00:11:07,935
but as the woman I am now.

170
00:11:09,205 --> 00:11:10,605
You'd remember me like that, right?

171
00:11:12,545 --> 00:11:14,775
I'm not really doing the world any good.

172
00:11:16,585 --> 00:11:18,245
Is there any reason for me to keep living?

173
00:11:43,205 --> 00:11:45,345
- Hey.
- You're up?

174
00:11:45,345 --> 00:11:46,345
Yes.

175
00:11:47,345 --> 00:11:48,375
I need you to come over.

176
00:11:49,275 --> 00:11:50,515
Are you not feeling well?

177
00:11:51,145 --> 00:11:52,785
No, but still.

178
00:11:54,855 --> 00:11:57,125
I'm out of town,
so it'll take three or four hours.

179
00:11:58,385 --> 00:11:59,795
A business trip on the weekend?

180
00:12:00,295 --> 00:12:02,795
No, I'll explain when I get there.

181
00:12:02,795 --> 00:12:03,795
Okay.

182
00:12:13,475 --> 00:12:14,875
Can I say we came together?

183
00:12:15,305 --> 00:12:16,305
Of course.

184
00:12:17,105 --> 00:12:18,505
It's not because of some bad press, is it?

185
00:12:21,575 --> 00:12:22,575
Look it up.

186
00:12:26,455 --> 00:12:28,555
Set up a meeting with CEO Ha Yong Joong.

187
00:12:28,615 --> 00:12:29,885
Tonight will work too.

188
00:12:31,725 --> 00:12:32,725
Why?

189
00:12:33,595 --> 00:12:34,825
You should be there too.

190
00:12:41,495 --> 00:12:45,065
Momo asked for a meeting with you,
but she wouldn't say why.

191
00:12:45,665 --> 00:12:47,035
How about lunch tomorrow?

192
00:12:48,075 --> 00:12:49,545
My brother is supposed to
come over tomorrow.

193
00:13:04,055 --> 00:13:05,085
A real gift.

194
00:13:21,105 --> 00:13:22,135
Was that a gift?

195
00:13:22,805 --> 00:13:24,675
You don't usually wear accessories.

196
00:13:25,705 --> 00:13:28,245
He brought it back for me from Japan.

197
00:13:30,545 --> 00:13:32,145
You didn't order wine.

198
00:13:32,415 --> 00:13:33,815
You can't be drinking.

199
00:13:34,285 --> 00:13:35,285
I'm going to drink.

200
00:13:39,025 --> 00:13:41,055
Is something wrong
between you and Director Shin?

201
00:13:44,965 --> 00:13:47,035
- Is there anything you need?
- I'll do the wine pairing.

202
00:13:47,095 --> 00:13:50,705
- Yes. We offer 4 and 5-glass options.
- Six glasses.

203
00:13:50,705 --> 00:13:51,735
Of course.

204
00:13:56,605 --> 00:13:58,975
Please be my big brother,

205
00:14:00,245 --> 00:14:01,445
like a real big brother.

206
00:14:03,915 --> 00:14:05,145
He hit me.

207
00:14:06,885 --> 00:14:08,015
Director Shin did?

208
00:14:09,255 --> 00:14:11,855
He thinks he can treat me this way
because I have no one left.

209
00:14:13,055 --> 00:14:14,625
Why? What happened?

210
00:14:20,465 --> 00:14:22,035
I had a miscarriage,

211
00:14:23,365 --> 00:14:24,835
and he accused me of getting
an abortion on purpose.

212
00:14:25,765 --> 00:14:26,905
You had a miscarriage?

213
00:14:27,505 --> 00:14:29,535
Seriously? Ju Shin?

214
00:14:32,145 --> 00:14:33,615
He's gone completely insane.

215
00:14:35,315 --> 00:14:36,345
Where did he hit you?

216
00:14:36,885 --> 00:14:37,945
My face.

217
00:14:38,985 --> 00:14:40,085
My cheek...

218
00:14:45,685 --> 00:14:48,125
But Director Shin is usually
so level-headed.

219
00:14:48,355 --> 00:14:51,765
There are things you just don't lie about.
Why would I make this up?

220
00:14:52,825 --> 00:14:55,435
Are you okay?
Shouldn't you be in the hospital?

221
00:14:58,105 --> 00:14:59,365
I've recovered now.

222
00:14:59,875 --> 00:15:02,535
But it's the emotional pain
I'll never forget.

223
00:15:03,205 --> 00:15:05,345
They say you shouldn't even
hit someone with a flower.

224
00:15:06,675 --> 00:15:08,545
I've never been hit before,
not even for an acting role.

225
00:15:11,015 --> 00:15:12,785
What about in "A Maiden's Prayer"?

226
00:15:14,085 --> 00:15:15,185
You think they hit for real?

227
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,255
It's all show.

228
00:15:19,795 --> 00:15:20,995
I think I'm going to call off
the engagement.

229
00:15:21,895 --> 00:15:24,065
- That's ridiculous.
- Why is it ridiculous?

230
00:15:24,325 --> 00:15:26,835
Most engaged couples fight a few times.

231
00:15:27,235 --> 00:15:30,005
It wasn't a verbal argument.
I'm telling you, he hit me.

232
00:15:32,305 --> 00:15:33,335
He apologized, right?

233
00:15:34,105 --> 00:15:35,375
A single, insincere word.

234
00:15:36,475 --> 00:15:39,445
I think it's better to end things now
than to get married and divorce later.

235
00:15:40,345 --> 00:15:41,445
Don't say that.

236
00:15:41,575 --> 00:15:43,115
There's no one like him.

237
00:15:43,115 --> 00:15:44,285
In what way?

238
00:15:44,815 --> 00:15:47,315
- He's perfect in every...
- You try getting hit.

239
00:15:48,055 --> 00:15:49,585
You know what that's like,
the humiliation.

240
00:15:52,855 --> 00:15:54,595
I heard you got beaten up a lot in school.

241
00:15:56,925 --> 00:15:58,295
When did I ever say that?

242
00:16:01,135 --> 00:16:02,465
Did you hear that from Kim Jin Ju?

243
00:16:02,665 --> 00:16:03,835
Does that matter?

244
00:16:07,505 --> 00:16:11,105
You should also try to see it
from Ju Shin's point of view.

245
00:16:15,915 --> 00:16:17,145
And what's his point of view?

246
00:16:18,285 --> 00:16:21,015
Since men can't just decide
to have a child,

247
00:16:21,485 --> 00:16:22,855
when it comes to their own bloodline...

248
00:16:23,485 --> 00:16:25,355
I wouldn't call it an obsession, exactly,

249
00:16:26,495 --> 00:16:27,755
but I'm sure
his expectations were very high.

250
00:16:28,925 --> 00:16:30,665
He's probably just blaming himself inside.

251
00:16:31,665 --> 00:16:34,365
I wish you wouldn't defend him
just because he's your friend.

252
00:16:36,195 --> 00:16:37,705
I've completely lost
all my feelings for him.

253
00:16:42,635 --> 00:16:45,345
Please, you're like a brother to me.
Help me.

254
00:16:48,245 --> 00:16:51,015
Are you really thinking of
calling off the engagement?

255
00:16:52,245 --> 00:16:53,355
I'm just an outsider.

256
00:16:54,185 --> 00:16:56,115
If I get involved, it could backfire.

257
00:16:57,625 --> 00:16:59,325
And Ju Shin is an incredibly proud man.

258
00:16:59,385 --> 00:17:01,325
That's exactly why
I decided to end things.

259
00:17:02,095 --> 00:17:05,695
Who doesn't have pride?
Is he the only one who gets to be proud?

260
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:07,435
And I'm Momo!

261
00:17:12,205 --> 00:17:13,205
Yong Joong.

262
00:17:19,545 --> 00:17:20,545
All this time,

263
00:17:21,315 --> 00:17:23,445
I've actually been jealous of her
at times.

264
00:17:25,945 --> 00:17:27,855
I have no one left now.

265
00:17:35,755 --> 00:17:37,865
What did you think
when you first met Momo?

266
00:17:38,765 --> 00:17:40,265
She was even prettier in person, right?

267
00:17:40,835 --> 00:17:42,595
You think men only care
about a pretty face?

268
00:17:43,365 --> 00:17:44,365
They don't?

269
00:17:44,965 --> 00:17:45,965
I don't...

270
00:17:47,475 --> 00:17:49,105
Did Momo tell you
her first impression of me?

271
00:17:50,605 --> 00:17:52,375
- Yes.
- What did she say?

272
00:17:52,875 --> 00:17:53,975
I know she wasn't impressed.

273
00:17:56,015 --> 00:17:59,545
Not "unimpressed."
She saw it as just a courtesy meeting.

274
00:17:59,815 --> 00:18:01,585
She only went because of James.

275
00:18:02,515 --> 00:18:04,325
I was drawn to her unique vibe.

276
00:18:06,155 --> 00:18:07,925
First, I fell for
her insane acting skills.

277
00:18:09,555 --> 00:18:10,565
Me too.

278
00:18:12,825 --> 00:18:14,595
She has this innocent audacity.

279
00:18:15,235 --> 00:18:17,135
How should I put it?
She's wise beyond her years.

280
00:18:21,075 --> 00:18:22,175
How is Momo...

281
00:18:23,845 --> 00:18:24,845
now?

282
00:18:26,145 --> 00:18:27,145
Lately.

283
00:18:35,485 --> 00:18:38,685
If I were your real sister,
what would you do in this situation?

284
00:18:39,225 --> 00:18:41,595
Would you just push me
to go through with the marriage?

285
00:18:43,665 --> 00:18:45,125
It's something you have to address
and move past.

286
00:18:46,495 --> 00:18:48,395
I really can't get married like this.

287
00:18:51,205 --> 00:18:52,235
(James)

288
00:18:53,305 --> 00:18:54,705
It's my brother. I should take this.

289
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:57,845
- Hey, James.
- Get over here, quick!

290
00:18:57,905 --> 00:18:59,575
- What's wrong?
- What am I going to do?

291
00:19:02,815 --> 00:19:04,715
- Something happened.
- Go on, you should check on him.

292
00:19:06,385 --> 00:19:07,555
We'll talk later...

293
00:19:19,895 --> 00:19:20,995
Why aren't you saying anything?

294
00:19:21,495 --> 00:19:22,765
You got hit once.

295
00:19:23,265 --> 00:19:24,965
But Director Shin lost his child.

296
00:19:25,465 --> 00:19:27,305
He hit me because I miscarried.

297
00:19:28,005 --> 00:19:30,205
I told you that you shouldn't be swimming.

298
00:19:30,545 --> 00:19:32,675
From his perspective, it's understandable
that he would be angry.

299
00:19:34,075 --> 00:19:35,145
Are you in love with him?

300
00:19:36,075 --> 00:19:37,845
Why are you so quick to defend him?

301
00:19:37,845 --> 00:19:39,515
How can you even say that?

302
00:19:39,585 --> 00:19:42,215
What about you? I said he hit me.

303
00:19:42,215 --> 00:19:44,355
You think it's because I went swimming,
just like he said?

304
00:19:44,655 --> 00:19:47,425
Shouldn't you feel for me and be worried,
like Yong Joong is?

305
00:19:54,265 --> 00:19:56,735
- I'm sorry, that's not what I meant...
- Forget it.

306
00:19:57,205 --> 00:19:59,335
- I was so excited to be an aunt...
- I said forget it.

307
00:20:08,915 --> 00:20:11,015
Ever since CEO Hyun passed away...

308
00:20:12,885 --> 00:20:13,885
Since then?

309
00:20:14,455 --> 00:20:15,455
She's been a little...

310
00:20:16,055 --> 00:20:17,685
on edge, I guess?

311
00:20:18,425 --> 00:20:21,825
Once she gets married and has a baby,
she'll be our lovely Momo again.

312
00:20:23,525 --> 00:20:24,565
Lovely Momo?

313
00:20:27,365 --> 00:20:28,395
Do you have a nickname?

314
00:20:28,795 --> 00:20:30,605
- Me?
- Yes.

315
00:20:30,735 --> 00:20:32,565
- No.
- Not even as a kid?

316
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:36,135
At the orphanage, they called me a crybaby
because I cried a lot.

317
00:20:38,675 --> 00:20:39,675
What about now?

318
00:20:41,015 --> 00:20:43,145
- Almost never...
- No reason to cry?

319
00:20:43,145 --> 00:20:44,215
Or did you get tough?

320
00:20:45,315 --> 00:20:46,385
Your tenderloin steak.

321
00:20:49,715 --> 00:20:50,855
By any chance,

322
00:20:51,485 --> 00:20:53,155
do you remember Ji An Hee?

323
00:20:53,455 --> 00:20:55,625
- From high school.
- Of course I remember him.

324
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:58,965
Everyone at school knew who he was.
He was the top dog.

325
00:21:03,665 --> 00:21:04,665
I heard he died, right?

326
00:21:05,935 --> 00:21:06,935
Yes.

327
00:21:09,175 --> 00:21:11,775
He's the reason
I stopped crying all the time.

328
00:21:13,275 --> 00:21:14,375
I guess he was good for something.

329
00:21:15,715 --> 00:21:16,715
Yong Joong...

330
00:21:17,245 --> 00:21:19,715
didn't go to college because he lost
interest in studying, thanks to Ji An Hee.

331
00:21:21,755 --> 00:21:24,825
But it all worked out for the best
in the end for him.

332
00:21:25,185 --> 00:21:26,285
He could've done even better.

333
00:21:27,395 --> 00:21:29,895
A college degree doesn't mean
that much these days.

334
00:21:30,365 --> 00:21:31,625
If it's so meaningless, why did you go?

335
00:21:31,965 --> 00:21:33,765
I started with nothing.

336
00:21:34,535 --> 00:21:36,865
When you have nothing,
you at least need an education.

337
00:21:42,005 --> 00:21:43,475
Do you really want a brother?

338
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:44,875
Of course.

339
00:21:45,745 --> 00:21:48,315
- I don't have any ulterior motives.
- I wasn't asking if you had any.

340
00:21:50,745 --> 00:21:51,785
Are you feeling insecure?

341
00:21:52,345 --> 00:21:53,855
Worried he'll give me more attention?

342
00:21:57,825 --> 00:21:59,325
Think whatever you want.

343
00:22:01,955 --> 00:22:03,465
She must be so insecure.

344
00:22:04,065 --> 00:22:05,725
What's she going do if I latch onto him?

345
00:22:09,035 --> 00:22:10,105
An endorphin rush.

346
00:22:27,815 --> 00:22:30,525
I don't think we should call the police.
It'll just cause problems.

347
00:22:30,985 --> 00:22:34,355
Exactly.
What if it hits the news sites right away?

348
00:22:35,755 --> 00:22:37,025
Both of the watches?

349
00:22:37,025 --> 00:22:39,665
The Bvlgari bracelet and Milano pouch...

350
00:22:40,265 --> 00:22:41,535
I really treasured those.

351
00:22:44,265 --> 00:22:46,235
You should put your valuables
in a safe deposit box...

352
00:22:46,635 --> 00:22:48,075
and just move back in
to the Cheongdam villa.

353
00:22:48,405 --> 00:22:50,975
I told you,
I'm not meant to live in a nice place.

354
00:22:51,175 --> 00:22:52,475
What kind of superstition is that?

355
00:22:52,605 --> 00:22:54,575
You still got robbed living here.

356
00:22:56,345 --> 00:22:58,245
It's better than losing my health.

357
00:22:58,845 --> 00:23:01,585
Then think of it as getting your bad luck
out of the way by losing your things.

358
00:23:01,785 --> 00:23:03,985
It's true what they say.
Ten guards can't stop one thief.

359
00:23:10,295 --> 00:23:11,465
Do you have a lot of friends from college?

360
00:23:12,465 --> 00:23:13,495
A fair amount.

361
00:23:14,065 --> 00:23:15,235
No real close friends, though.

362
00:23:16,095 --> 00:23:17,565
That's probably because
you don't open up first.

363
00:23:18,335 --> 00:23:19,365
How did you know?

364
00:23:19,935 --> 00:23:21,935
- You just seem that way.
- It's the other way around.

365
00:23:22,335 --> 00:23:24,005
They act friendly to my face,

366
00:23:24,005 --> 00:23:25,205
but they are the ones
keeping their distance.

367
00:23:25,375 --> 00:23:26,745
It could just be your own insecurities.

368
00:23:28,575 --> 00:23:29,575
I'm...

369
00:23:30,185 --> 00:23:31,615
not senseless.

370
00:23:33,115 --> 00:23:35,215
Sounds like Kim Jin Ju
was your only best friend.

371
00:23:36,755 --> 00:23:37,755
You must miss her.

372
00:23:44,525 --> 00:23:45,595
Have you forgotten her already?

373
00:23:52,235 --> 00:23:53,505
How could I ever forget her?

374
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:56,605
It still doesn't feel real.

375
00:23:57,545 --> 00:24:00,875
She wasn't the type
to give up on life that easily.

376
00:24:04,315 --> 00:24:05,615
There are two types of people.

377
00:24:06,685 --> 00:24:10,625
There's a type who, when a loved one dies,
blames themself for what they did wrong.

378
00:24:11,025 --> 00:24:14,325
And the type who only recalls good things
and gets trapped in their grief.

379
00:24:15,855 --> 00:24:16,895
Which one are you?

380
00:24:18,825 --> 00:24:19,865
I wouldn't say...

381
00:24:21,095 --> 00:24:22,335
I miss her all that much.

382
00:24:22,595 --> 00:24:23,865
Sounds like you have some hard feelings.

383
00:24:25,365 --> 00:24:27,505
Everyone has different sides to them.

384
00:24:28,605 --> 00:24:29,735
So she had a lot of faults?

385
00:24:30,945 --> 00:24:32,075
Is that what it sounded like?

386
00:24:32,775 --> 00:24:33,775
Yes.

387
00:24:36,075 --> 00:24:37,145
What about you?

388
00:24:37,885 --> 00:24:38,885
Your parents...

389
00:24:40,515 --> 00:24:41,515
As for me,

390
00:24:42,115 --> 00:24:44,355
I don't have any guilt.

391
00:24:44,425 --> 00:24:45,955
I don't think I ever disappointed them.

392
00:24:46,355 --> 00:24:47,655
At least, that's what I think.

393
00:24:48,795 --> 00:24:51,825
Kim Jin Ju really liked you.

394
00:24:52,465 --> 00:24:54,735
All the kids at the home did,
but she especially liked you.

395
00:24:56,435 --> 00:24:57,465
Never mind people.

396
00:24:58,335 --> 00:24:59,635
What do women like?

397
00:25:00,905 --> 00:25:01,935
What are they into?

398
00:25:03,135 --> 00:25:04,345
So many things.

399
00:25:05,405 --> 00:25:06,405
What about you, Geum Ba Ra?

400
00:25:07,315 --> 00:25:09,215
I deliberately tried
not to think about it.

401
00:25:10,015 --> 00:25:12,845
I hate the feeling
of wanting things I can't have.

402
00:25:15,285 --> 00:25:16,315
That's kind of sad.

403
00:25:16,815 --> 00:25:19,625
Think about it, and if there's anything
you want, let me know.

404
00:25:20,795 --> 00:25:22,255
You even made time for me
when you were busy.

405
00:25:23,425 --> 00:25:24,465
It was the least I could do.

406
00:25:25,225 --> 00:25:26,525
That's beside the point.

407
00:25:26,895 --> 00:25:28,835
You're always taking me
to nice places like this.

408
00:25:29,635 --> 00:25:31,165
But you treated me to a meal last time.

409
00:25:31,465 --> 00:25:33,405
You might think less of me for this,

410
00:25:34,075 --> 00:25:35,075
but to be honest,

411
00:25:35,075 --> 00:25:37,045
I'm not really used to being
on the receiving end.

412
00:25:37,745 --> 00:25:40,945
As you said, it might be a bit
of an inferiority complex.

413
00:25:43,275 --> 00:25:44,985
Do you know the difference
between a bribe and charity?

414
00:25:45,445 --> 00:25:48,985
A bribe is given for a specific purpose,

415
00:25:50,115 --> 00:25:52,155
- while charity is just given.
- Right.

416
00:25:52,425 --> 00:25:53,925
A veteran congressman,
who'd received a lot of funds,

417
00:25:53,925 --> 00:25:55,055
was once asked a question.

418
00:25:55,725 --> 00:25:58,525
"How do you take money
without any repercussions?"

419
00:25:59,465 --> 00:26:00,835
And the veteran congressman replied,

420
00:26:01,495 --> 00:26:03,805
"You have to debone it carefully
so you don't choke."

421
00:26:04,205 --> 00:26:06,865
When they asked how to debone it,
he said that was his secret.

422
00:26:07,975 --> 00:26:11,075
"You just have to eat boneless whale meat.
The whale is the conglomerate."

423
00:26:15,575 --> 00:26:18,545
Besides whales,
what other fish is boneless?

424
00:26:20,515 --> 00:26:22,555
- An octopus?
- Exactly.

425
00:26:23,455 --> 00:26:25,485
The octopus is money from a faction boss.

426
00:26:25,625 --> 00:26:27,555
And aren't I basically your faction boss?

427
00:26:30,095 --> 00:26:31,525
So you can get used to
accepting things from me.

428
00:26:33,065 --> 00:26:34,395
I'll think about it.

429
00:26:35,535 --> 00:26:36,565
You should smile more often.

430
00:26:37,205 --> 00:26:38,205
You too, Director.

431
00:26:38,605 --> 00:26:39,605
I'm a man.

432
00:26:40,205 --> 00:26:42,135
What's gender got to do with smiling?

433
00:26:42,905 --> 00:26:44,175
It makes me look frivolous.

434
00:26:44,175 --> 00:26:47,245
Are you strong? Or just pretending?

435
00:26:47,945 --> 00:26:49,475
I told you to smile, not to be cheeky.

436
00:26:50,075 --> 00:26:52,315
Is it cheeky to ask a question
I'm curious about?

437
00:26:54,885 --> 00:26:55,955
You're curious about me?

438
00:26:58,185 --> 00:26:59,625
You want to know more about me?

439
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:03,965
No.

440
00:27:05,695 --> 00:27:06,725
Is that your pride talking?

441
00:27:07,765 --> 00:27:08,765
A lack of interest?

442
00:27:09,035 --> 00:27:10,195
It's just that...

443
00:27:11,005 --> 00:27:13,035
you're someone
who grew up with a lot of love,

444
00:27:14,205 --> 00:27:15,905
but you seem so rigid.

445
00:27:20,045 --> 00:27:21,275
Did you hear about Momo's dream?

446
00:27:21,575 --> 00:27:23,515
- A conception dream.
- No.

447
00:27:24,645 --> 00:27:26,615
She said a giant yellow serpent
bit her on the shoulder.

448
00:27:28,985 --> 00:27:30,015
It must be a boy.

449
00:27:31,625 --> 00:27:33,655
My mother also had a dream
about a serpent before I was born.

450
00:27:34,525 --> 00:27:35,895
My sincerest congratulations.

451
00:27:39,265 --> 00:27:41,965
I turn someone lower than dirt
into a Cinderella,

452
00:27:42,995 --> 00:27:44,865
and she can't even properly
carry one child.

453
00:27:51,245 --> 00:27:53,145
I have no one left now.

454
00:28:05,385 --> 00:28:06,385
Right now?

455
00:28:09,225 --> 00:28:10,425
I'm out playing golf.

456
00:28:10,865 --> 00:28:11,925
And you feel like playing golf?

457
00:28:12,565 --> 00:28:13,625
You're the one who said I should learn.

458
00:28:14,135 --> 00:28:17,105
Right, you listen so well,
but go and swim your guts out...

459
00:28:18,035 --> 00:28:19,865
People change their tune
when they get what they want...

460
00:28:19,935 --> 00:28:21,235
You're not happy with me, are you?

461
00:28:22,005 --> 00:28:24,075
You regret operating on me, don't you?

462
00:28:24,705 --> 00:28:25,975
What do you want me to say?

463
00:28:26,045 --> 00:28:27,845
I want to do whatever you want.

464
00:28:30,815 --> 00:28:32,085
Let's have another baby, then.

465
00:28:33,715 --> 00:28:34,715
What's today's date?

466
00:28:34,715 --> 00:28:36,615
Let's just call off the engagement
and end it.

467
00:28:37,685 --> 00:28:39,225
I refuse to live my life being abused.

468
00:28:39,785 --> 00:28:41,325
I'm beneath you, Director.

469
00:28:41,325 --> 00:28:43,395
I'm just Momo on the outside.
I'm flawed and lacking...

470
00:28:43,455 --> 00:28:44,525
Are you serious?

471
00:28:45,425 --> 00:28:49,435
I think I'll get tired of
walking on eggshells around you.

472
00:28:50,805 --> 00:28:52,065
In fact, I'm already exhausted.

473
00:28:52,405 --> 00:28:54,735
How long has it even been
for you to feel that way...

474
00:28:54,805 --> 00:28:57,175
I'll keep your secret.
I'll take it to my grave.

475
00:29:03,175 --> 00:29:04,385
So what's your plan?

476
00:29:05,645 --> 00:29:07,255
I'll just keep living as Momo, I guess.

477
00:29:07,855 --> 00:29:09,085
Just don't act.

478
00:29:10,255 --> 00:29:11,485
Just shoot whatever commercials
come your way.

479
00:29:11,555 --> 00:29:13,925
I won't. Acting isn't for just anyone.

480
00:29:18,765 --> 00:29:19,925
You won't regret it?

481
00:29:20,325 --> 00:29:22,595
- What more is there to lose?
- Lose?

482
00:29:22,665 --> 00:29:25,565
- You have it all.
- I even gave up my own body.

483
00:29:29,375 --> 00:29:31,205
I'll have Geum Ba Ra release the story.

484
00:29:32,575 --> 00:29:34,675
Excited at the thought of
having the world at your feet?

485
00:29:37,485 --> 00:29:40,345
I told you, I'll live quietly.
I won't cause you any trouble.

486
00:29:43,415 --> 00:29:45,625
Yes, a little more toward the camera.

487
00:29:50,255 --> 00:29:52,765
Momo, a bigger smile, okay?

488
00:29:58,935 --> 00:29:59,935
Yes.

489
00:30:00,635 --> 00:30:03,005
That's great.
You're starting to loosen up.

490
00:30:04,675 --> 00:30:06,105
Yes, look at the camera more.

491
00:30:07,445 --> 00:30:08,745
Okay.

492
00:30:11,485 --> 00:30:15,715
To Kim Jin Ju, Director Shin is
a deity or her Prince Charming.

493
00:30:16,155 --> 00:30:18,785
- Now, I...
- We're good.

494
00:30:25,765 --> 00:30:27,495
Momo is pretty. I'll give her that.

495
00:30:28,765 --> 00:30:29,795
We're rolling.

496
00:30:30,705 --> 00:30:32,405
Are we working through dinner?

497
00:30:34,035 --> 00:30:37,945
I sat in on the meeting
with Ba Ra and Momo last weekend.

498
00:30:40,275 --> 00:30:42,775
I know you must've been
frustrated and upset,

499
00:30:44,185 --> 00:30:45,915
but still, did you have to
hit her in the face?

500
00:30:46,945 --> 00:30:48,155
That's enough.

501
00:30:48,585 --> 00:30:49,855
Haven't you heard
we're ending the engagement?

502
00:30:52,625 --> 00:30:53,625
We're going to.

503
00:30:55,325 --> 00:30:56,325
It was her idea.

504
00:30:59,795 --> 00:31:01,265
You two were crazy about each other.

505
00:31:02,595 --> 00:31:05,205
I know you don't really show
your feelings much, but...

506
00:31:07,705 --> 00:31:09,335
People's feelings really do change.

507
00:31:10,305 --> 00:31:11,475
They're bound to.

508
00:31:12,475 --> 00:31:14,475
You know how James
can't even take care of himself...

509
00:31:14,475 --> 00:31:16,015
and calls himself a relationship expert?

510
00:31:16,215 --> 00:31:18,115
He says when a woman wants to break up,

511
00:31:18,315 --> 00:31:20,585
it's actually a plea for more attention,

512
00:31:21,155 --> 00:31:22,615
more care, and more love.

513
00:31:24,425 --> 00:31:26,825
Forcing yourself to feel something
isn't love.

514
00:31:27,755 --> 00:31:28,755
Okay.

515
00:31:31,325 --> 00:31:33,825
Yes, look right into the camera. More!

516
00:31:34,265 --> 00:31:35,565
I'm so hot.

517
00:31:35,635 --> 00:31:38,005
If I hold out my hand, who could resist?

518
00:31:38,205 --> 00:31:40,335
They'd be tripping over themselves
with gratitude.

519
00:31:40,775 --> 00:31:43,275
Ha Yong Joong is actually kind of great.

520
00:31:46,305 --> 00:31:48,045
Do you ever think about your first love?

521
00:31:49,315 --> 00:31:51,185
I don't have a first love
worth remembering.

522
00:31:51,615 --> 00:31:53,085
You dated a lot in high school.

523
00:31:53,415 --> 00:31:54,915
Only two of them were serious.

524
00:31:56,215 --> 00:31:57,655
My first love...

525
00:31:58,385 --> 00:31:59,455
was Ba Ra.

526
00:32:00,825 --> 00:32:02,355
She was just a little kid,

527
00:32:03,325 --> 00:32:06,025
but I could never forget her.
She'd pop into my head now and then.

528
00:32:10,235 --> 00:32:13,735
And then that little kid appeared,
all grown into a lady.

529
00:32:15,375 --> 00:32:17,345
She's just a kid to me.

530
00:32:18,005 --> 00:32:19,575
First impressions are everything.

531
00:32:20,875 --> 00:32:22,475
She was so young and small...

532
00:32:22,915 --> 00:32:25,215
that I thought she was a 5 or 6-year-old
kindergartener.

533
00:32:25,945 --> 00:32:27,385
If you say so.

534
00:32:31,855 --> 00:32:33,285
Is it really over for good?

535
00:32:35,925 --> 00:32:37,255
You'll probably see her now and then.

536
00:32:37,625 --> 00:32:38,925
Doesn't look like it.

537
00:32:41,165 --> 00:32:42,795
It'll just make for some messy headlines,
that's all.

538
00:32:43,865 --> 00:32:45,935
Was it that easy to just call it quits?

539
00:32:48,105 --> 00:32:50,335
Can I come with you to Yong Joong's place?

540
00:32:51,775 --> 00:32:52,775
Why?

541
00:32:53,675 --> 00:32:54,675
Now?

542
00:32:54,675 --> 00:32:56,975
I suddenly really miss Pickles.

543
00:32:58,985 --> 00:33:00,215
I'll take you.

544
00:33:09,925 --> 00:33:12,065
You sure Yong Joong won't mind?

545
00:33:12,325 --> 00:33:13,695
He's not home yet.

546
00:33:15,065 --> 00:33:16,635
Is he seeing anyone?

547
00:33:19,165 --> 00:33:20,605
No. Not that I know of.

548
00:33:20,905 --> 00:33:24,905
I can't believe he's single.
He's such a catch.

549
00:33:27,175 --> 00:33:29,875
Run the story. "Momo and Shin Ju Shin
End Their Engagement."

550
00:33:48,695 --> 00:33:51,165
(Exclusive: Momo and Director Shin Ju Shin
End Engagement)

551
00:33:54,635 --> 00:33:57,845
Goodness, look at you,
landing an exclusive on your last day.

552
00:33:59,845 --> 00:34:02,245
Take the year off,
but you have to come back.

553
00:34:03,145 --> 00:34:04,685
So what caused the split?

554
00:34:05,385 --> 00:34:08,015
- They didn't really have a fight.
- You can't be serious.

555
00:34:08,385 --> 00:34:10,285
Just as it says in the article,
they couldn't get married happily...

556
00:34:10,285 --> 00:34:12,625
after all they've been through.

557
00:34:12,685 --> 00:34:13,955
So they decided to call it off.

558
00:34:13,955 --> 00:34:15,525
Who made the final call?

559
00:34:16,295 --> 00:34:17,695
It was mutual.

560
00:34:17,695 --> 00:34:19,425
It's like how you can just sense...

561
00:34:19,425 --> 00:34:21,435
that the feelings aren't
what they used to be.

562
00:34:21,835 --> 00:34:24,465
I bet it was Shin Ju Shin
who started to lose interest.

563
00:34:24,835 --> 00:34:27,735
- You heard something?
- A distant relative of mine...

564
00:34:27,835 --> 00:34:31,305
apparently went to the same college
and was in the same major as Momo's mom.

565
00:34:32,445 --> 00:34:36,675
But she apparently got pregnant
her freshman year and dropped out.

566
00:34:36,775 --> 00:34:39,315
Then one day, she pops up on TV
as Momo's mother.

567
00:34:39,385 --> 00:34:40,815
So she really is a college dropout.

568
00:34:41,015 --> 00:34:42,385
So she got married young?

569
00:34:42,515 --> 00:34:46,385
If she'd had the baby from back then,
they say the kid would be much older...

570
00:34:46,455 --> 00:34:48,695
- than Momo.
- So what's the story?

571
00:34:48,755 --> 00:34:50,295
It means she has a past.

572
00:34:51,225 --> 00:34:54,495
Shin Ju Shin comes
from a prestigious family of doctors,

573
00:34:54,565 --> 00:34:57,165
but Momo's pedigree
doesn't really measure up.

574
00:34:57,365 --> 00:34:58,805
What's wrong with Momo's background?

575
00:34:58,805 --> 00:35:00,305
She's the only daughter of Sun Gallery.

576
00:35:00,405 --> 00:35:03,075
- Momo's mom is his second wife.
- Really?

577
00:35:04,375 --> 00:35:06,275
His first wife died soon
after their wedding.

578
00:35:06,275 --> 00:35:07,545
They had no children.

579
00:35:08,015 --> 00:35:09,515
It's not public knowledge.

580
00:35:09,575 --> 00:35:12,985
I got curious and looked it up
while on the art beat.

581
00:35:13,045 --> 00:35:16,515
There's a huge age gap, too.
Something like 16 years.

582
00:35:16,715 --> 00:35:19,125
- Almost 20 years, actually.
- My gosh.

583
00:35:19,525 --> 00:35:20,995
So what happened to the baby?

584
00:35:21,495 --> 00:35:23,325
Doesn't that mean Momo has a half-sister?

585
00:35:23,395 --> 00:35:26,725
No, it means same mother,
different father.

586
00:35:28,095 --> 00:35:29,665
She might not have had the baby.

587
00:35:30,395 --> 00:35:33,135
You two are close.
Has she ever mentioned a big sister?

588
00:35:34,335 --> 00:35:36,305
- No.
- Why would she?

589
00:35:36,435 --> 00:35:39,145
She might not even know.

590
00:35:39,705 --> 00:35:40,805
That makes sense.

591
00:35:41,615 --> 00:35:43,175
I wouldn't bring it up either
if I were her.

592
00:35:53,885 --> 00:35:54,895
Where's Pickles?

593
00:35:55,425 --> 00:35:56,595
At Reporter Geum's place?

594
00:35:56,595 --> 00:35:59,565
No, Momo's watching him for a while.

595
00:35:59,695 --> 00:36:01,195
That's what I came to talk about.

596
00:36:02,365 --> 00:36:03,565
So, what are you going to do about it?

597
00:36:04,605 --> 00:36:06,965
- About what?
- You know what I mean.

598
00:36:07,135 --> 00:36:08,705
Now that they've
called off the engagement...

599
00:36:10,035 --> 00:36:12,105
I can't exactly ask either of them.

600
00:36:12,805 --> 00:36:14,475
Aren't you the one who caused it?

601
00:36:14,775 --> 00:36:16,015
No, I'm not.

602
00:36:16,515 --> 00:36:18,045
You're tempted, aren't you?

603
00:36:18,315 --> 00:36:20,285
What? There's nothing to be tempted by.

604
00:36:20,485 --> 00:36:22,455
You don't sound so sure.

605
00:36:24,255 --> 00:36:25,725
Momo is absolutely off-limits.

606
00:36:28,855 --> 00:36:30,425
I hate to even bring this up,

607
00:36:31,025 --> 00:36:33,195
but Ju Shin even got Momo pregnant.

608
00:36:33,325 --> 00:36:35,835
An OB-GYN I know told me in confidence.

609
00:36:36,165 --> 00:36:37,635
Was the doctor a woman?

610
00:36:37,905 --> 00:36:39,705
What does their gender matter?

611
00:36:40,235 --> 00:36:41,535
Don't change the subject.

612
00:36:42,335 --> 00:36:46,075
You have a real knack for making things up
and jumping to conclusions.

613
00:36:47,875 --> 00:36:48,875
You think I'm making this up?

614
00:36:50,985 --> 00:36:51,985
Can't you answer me?

615
00:36:52,485 --> 00:36:54,755
I haven't even thought
about something like that.

616
00:36:55,155 --> 00:36:56,685
Don't start now.

617
00:36:57,215 --> 00:36:58,585
And don't you dare change your mind.

618
00:36:59,655 --> 00:37:01,125
I have a bad feeling about this.

619
00:37:01,655 --> 00:37:03,225
Your hunches are never right.

620
00:37:03,225 --> 00:37:05,025
Please.

621
00:37:05,395 --> 00:37:07,325
It's all up to you.

622
00:37:08,665 --> 00:37:10,765
We've got to go for round two, right?

623
00:37:10,765 --> 00:37:12,605
Of course!

624
00:37:13,635 --> 00:37:16,375
You're the guest of honor! Don't leave.

625
00:37:16,505 --> 00:37:17,945
I won't.

626
00:37:18,305 --> 00:37:20,545
Come on, none of us has ever heard
Geum Ba Ra sing.

627
00:37:20,805 --> 00:37:21,815
That's right.

628
00:37:22,115 --> 00:37:24,415
You're better off not hearing me sing.

629
00:37:24,815 --> 00:37:27,915
We'll be the judge of
whether it's noise or music.

630
00:37:28,785 --> 00:37:31,355
- I think I'll just stick to my day job.
- Backup dancing?

631
00:37:31,355 --> 00:37:32,355
Right.

632
00:37:32,825 --> 00:37:36,025
I'm the real, real deal

633
00:37:36,095 --> 00:37:38,825
Totally the real deal

634
00:37:39,065 --> 00:37:40,595
(Century's Love... Century's Breakup?)

635
00:37:40,595 --> 00:37:42,165
(Momo loses fiance
after losing her mother)

636
00:37:42,235 --> 00:37:43,835
(Exclusive: Momo and Director Shin Ju Shin
End Engagement)

637
00:37:43,965 --> 00:37:45,505
(Exclusive: Momo and Director Shin Ju Shin
End Engagement)

638
00:38:07,625 --> 00:38:09,955
Do you think your daddy will
call tomorrow?

639
00:38:10,325 --> 00:38:11,365
He will, right?

640
00:38:23,435 --> 00:38:25,105
Want some? You thirsty?

641
00:38:27,475 --> 00:38:30,415
I'm Lucky, and you're Lucky, too.

642
00:38:33,245 --> 00:38:34,815
I'm not Momo.

643
00:38:35,385 --> 00:38:38,755
I'm Jin Ju. Kim Jin Ju.

644
00:39:05,945 --> 00:39:06,985
When did you get here?

645
00:39:07,285 --> 00:39:08,855
You should've just come in
or rung the doorbell.

646
00:39:24,735 --> 00:39:26,235
I've been drinking.

647
00:39:26,535 --> 00:39:27,565
Good for you.

648
00:39:28,305 --> 00:39:29,535
A lot...

649
00:39:30,335 --> 00:39:32,605
Feeling rough? Nauseous?

650
00:39:33,345 --> 00:39:34,345
I don't know.

651
00:39:35,375 --> 00:39:36,815
I feel awful.

652
00:39:55,635 --> 00:39:57,495
Ice water, iced coffee, or honey water?

653
00:40:14,415 --> 00:40:15,485
Sorry.

654
00:40:17,385 --> 00:40:19,785
I'll get out of your hair in a bit.

655
00:40:20,455 --> 00:40:23,455
- Go on your run.
- I can skip a day.

656
00:40:25,525 --> 00:40:27,295
The pharmacy probably isn't open yet.

657
00:40:27,395 --> 00:40:30,635
It's not that bad. I'm okay.

658
00:40:32,905 --> 00:40:34,405
Is something wrong?

659
00:40:34,835 --> 00:40:36,275
A work dinner.

660
00:40:36,835 --> 00:40:38,005
It was for my leave.

661
00:40:38,405 --> 00:40:40,345
For now, just get some rest.

662
00:40:41,075 --> 00:40:44,245
If I didn't have work,
we could've gone somewhere for a few days.

663
00:40:47,645 --> 00:40:49,985
- Who's "we?"
- You and me, of course.

664
00:40:52,285 --> 00:40:54,155
That would be so nice.

665
00:40:54,955 --> 00:40:56,495
How about we go to Japan next month?

666
00:40:58,595 --> 00:41:00,265
But you've already been to Japan.

667
00:41:00,265 --> 00:41:01,595
You haven't been to China, have you?

668
00:41:02,965 --> 00:41:05,465
Everything's going your way.

669
00:41:06,135 --> 00:41:07,165
I'm so jealous.

670
00:41:09,235 --> 00:41:10,675
Have you talked to Momo?

671
00:41:12,275 --> 00:41:13,275
No.

672
00:41:13,275 --> 00:41:16,545
I wonder how Momo's feeling.

673
00:41:18,645 --> 00:41:20,045
She asked me to be
like an older brother to her.

674
00:41:21,515 --> 00:41:23,485
It's like I'm gaining a new little sister.

675
00:41:26,085 --> 00:41:27,485
A "little sister"...

676
00:41:30,495 --> 00:41:33,295
But you like her as a woman.

677
00:41:34,365 --> 00:41:35,735
I wouldn't go that far.

678
00:41:37,165 --> 00:41:38,965
You want to be in love with her,
don't you?

679
00:41:40,105 --> 00:41:41,505
Like, true love.

680
00:41:43,335 --> 00:41:45,405
One-sided feelings aren't true love.

681
00:41:49,115 --> 00:41:50,445
My little rascal comes first.

682
00:41:51,245 --> 00:41:52,615
Momo comes second.

683
00:41:54,385 --> 00:41:56,215
What if Momo starts to like you back?

684
00:41:57,285 --> 00:41:58,485
What if she falls for you?

685
00:42:00,855 --> 00:42:03,025
I'm Ju Shin's best friend.
That doesn't cross my mind.

686
00:42:04,255 --> 00:42:06,895
But you wouldn't have a reason
to turn her down, right?

687
00:42:12,735 --> 00:42:15,605
I don't think I could handle
seeing you two together.

688
00:42:18,405 --> 00:42:19,545
I'll leave.

689
00:42:20,905 --> 00:42:22,445
There you go again,
saying such hurtful things.

690
00:42:22,915 --> 00:42:23,945
Where would you go?

691
00:42:27,045 --> 00:42:28,455
You think I wouldn't be able to find you?

692
00:42:31,015 --> 00:42:33,455
Always pulling these little stunts.
Honestly, you big baby.

693
00:42:34,455 --> 00:42:36,155
How long are you going to see me as a kid?

694
00:42:36,425 --> 00:42:37,425
Forever.

695
00:42:38,125 --> 00:42:40,825
You by my side, and me by yours...

696
00:42:41,595 --> 00:42:43,065
We're going to grow old together.

697
00:42:44,365 --> 00:42:45,765
So stop with these spiteful thoughts.

698
00:42:47,735 --> 00:42:49,505
Momo has been so prickly with me lately.

699
00:42:50,475 --> 00:42:51,805
She's not the same Momo I used to know.

700
00:42:53,645 --> 00:42:54,715
Try to understand her.

701
00:42:55,675 --> 00:42:57,645
Anyone else would've had
a breakdown by now.

702
00:42:58,315 --> 00:42:59,685
Until she's had time to heal,

703
00:43:00,745 --> 00:43:02,555
be the big sister she can lean on.

704
00:43:03,015 --> 00:43:04,685
I'm only human and a woman.

705
00:43:05,755 --> 00:43:07,455
Don't I need someone to lean on?

706
00:43:13,965 --> 00:43:14,965
You have me.

707
00:43:16,565 --> 00:43:17,565
For one month...

708
00:43:18,135 --> 00:43:20,905
No, even for just one day,
I wish I could be your girlfriend.

709
00:43:21,205 --> 00:43:24,005
Next time you go drinking, call me.
I'll come pick you up.

710
00:43:24,745 --> 00:43:26,205
As if you have the time.

711
00:43:26,845 --> 00:43:28,315
I'd send my driver at least.

712
00:43:31,115 --> 00:43:32,145
I'll make you some hangover soup.

713
00:43:32,545 --> 00:43:34,685
- I'm going to sleep.
- Get some sleep first.

714
00:44:01,245 --> 00:44:04,175
I'll bring you something to wear,
so go wash up.

715
00:44:29,975 --> 00:44:30,975
You all right?

716
00:44:32,245 --> 00:44:34,305
- Yes.
- You're not dizzy?

717
00:44:35,815 --> 00:44:36,815
No.

718
00:44:37,315 --> 00:44:38,885
Careful now. Don't fall.

719
00:44:41,385 --> 00:44:42,385
Hey.

720
00:44:43,255 --> 00:44:44,255
Yes?

721
00:44:48,555 --> 00:44:51,695
What is it?
There's a new toothbrush in the cabinet.

722
00:45:00,265 --> 00:45:01,265
Are you feeling sick?

723
00:45:02,135 --> 00:45:03,135
No.

724
00:45:04,235 --> 00:45:05,245
Can you feel...

725
00:45:07,605 --> 00:45:09,775
the way I like you...

726
00:45:11,845 --> 00:45:12,845
and love you?

727
00:45:15,455 --> 00:45:16,655
Sometimes, I can't.

728
00:45:17,685 --> 00:45:18,955
But right now, I'm starting to.

729
00:45:24,195 --> 00:45:25,195
Sometimes...

730
00:45:28,095 --> 00:45:29,095
Sometimes what?

731
00:45:32,735 --> 00:45:33,735
Tell me.

732
00:45:35,305 --> 00:45:37,775
I feel like you don't really know
how I feel.

733
00:45:38,075 --> 00:45:39,345
That's my line.

734
00:45:40,405 --> 00:45:42,345
If that's how you really felt,
then I'm sorry.

735
00:45:42,815 --> 00:45:45,045
It's because I grew up with my brother.
Honestly...

736
00:45:45,845 --> 00:45:46,845
Speak of the devil.

737
00:45:47,685 --> 00:45:48,685
I left some clothes out for you.

738
00:45:50,215 --> 00:45:51,215
Hey, James.

739
00:45:57,525 --> 00:46:01,495
Last night I dreamed Oiji showed up,
but almost all of its fur had fallen out.

740
00:46:02,065 --> 00:46:03,395
You're still thinking about Oiji?

741
00:46:03,665 --> 00:46:05,765
Of course I am. When have I ever stopped?

742
00:46:06,135 --> 00:46:07,835
I think I should have
a memorial rite performed.

743
00:46:08,135 --> 00:46:10,205
Don't go overboard. It wasn't a person.

744
00:46:10,535 --> 00:46:12,705
You know how much Oiji meant to me.

745
00:46:13,005 --> 00:46:14,375
Not more than you, of course.

746
00:46:14,815 --> 00:46:15,815
Then just do it.

747
00:46:16,075 --> 00:46:17,245
You know a monk, don't you?

748
00:46:17,715 --> 00:46:18,985
You mean you're going to do it
at a temple?

749
00:46:19,885 --> 00:46:21,415
People will say
you're disrespecting Buddhism.

750
00:46:21,585 --> 00:46:25,085
Buddhism teaches compassion
for mute animals, especially dogs.

751
00:46:25,925 --> 00:46:28,455
Whatever. You figure it out.
I can't ask them to do that.

752
00:46:28,925 --> 00:46:30,625
- Oiji meant a lot to you too...
- I have to go for my workout.

753
00:46:30,925 --> 00:46:31,925
Hello?

754
00:46:32,265 --> 00:46:34,965
- It's good karma.
- Then you can build enough for us both.

755
00:46:35,035 --> 00:46:36,035
Hello?

756
00:46:37,565 --> 00:46:38,565
Darn it.

757
00:46:43,935 --> 00:46:44,945
Oh, Oiji.

758
00:46:46,205 --> 00:46:48,515
Is there anything I wouldn't do for you?

759
00:46:49,745 --> 00:46:52,285
What brings you here at the crack of dawn?

760
00:46:59,825 --> 00:47:01,185
(Momo)

761
00:47:01,255 --> 00:47:03,095
The phone is turned off.

762
00:47:03,225 --> 00:47:05,965
Please leave a message after the tone.

763
00:47:06,465 --> 00:47:07,465
Charges may apply...

764
00:47:07,525 --> 00:47:11,905
(Momo)

765
00:47:12,305 --> 00:47:14,205
The phone is turned off.

766
00:47:16,135 --> 00:47:19,245
Why is her phone off?
Who does she think she is?

767
00:47:21,945 --> 00:47:24,575
Don't you dare pee anywhere you want.
You'll get a spanking.

768
00:47:40,425 --> 00:47:41,425
Hello?

769
00:47:44,935 --> 00:47:45,935
Hello?

770
00:47:47,265 --> 00:47:48,275
Momo?

771
00:47:49,335 --> 00:47:50,335
Yes.

772
00:47:51,375 --> 00:47:53,145
I almost didn't answer
because it's an unknown number.

773
00:47:53,575 --> 00:47:55,875
I've been getting flooded
with calls and texts.

774
00:47:56,315 --> 00:47:57,545
So I turned off my main phone.

775
00:47:58,445 --> 00:47:59,445
I see.

776
00:48:01,985 --> 00:48:03,815
Is something wrong with Ba Ra?

777
00:48:04,285 --> 00:48:06,055
She's never turned her phone off before.

778
00:48:06,885 --> 00:48:08,055
She's sleeping.

779
00:48:08,055 --> 00:48:09,995
She said she drank a lot
at a work dinner last night.

780
00:48:11,595 --> 00:48:12,865
At your place?

781
00:48:14,195 --> 00:48:15,295
Yes.

782
00:48:15,495 --> 00:48:16,665
She'll call when she wakes up.

783
00:48:19,935 --> 00:48:23,135
Okay. Don't tell me they
took things to the next level.

784
00:48:25,275 --> 00:48:26,275
Things must be tough.

785
00:48:27,745 --> 00:48:28,975
I heard from Ju Shin.

786
00:48:34,915 --> 00:48:36,615
You can buy me a drink
to cheer me up sometime.

787
00:48:38,525 --> 00:48:39,525
Sure.

788
00:48:41,155 --> 00:48:43,395
Can I keep Pickles for a few more days?

789
00:48:44,795 --> 00:48:45,795
Of course.

790
00:48:47,425 --> 00:48:50,735
He helps take my mind off things.

791
00:48:53,765 --> 00:48:54,765
I'm glad to hear that.

792
00:48:58,445 --> 00:49:02,745
If you start having bad thoughts,
think of a good memory or listen to music.

793
00:49:06,415 --> 00:49:07,415
Okay.

794
00:49:11,055 --> 00:49:12,255
Should I save this number?

795
00:49:13,785 --> 00:49:14,785
Yes.

796
00:49:19,065 --> 00:49:20,095
Talk to you later.

797
00:49:21,165 --> 00:49:22,165
Okay.

798
00:49:54,065 --> 00:49:57,065
Grandfather says she died
and came back to life.

799
00:49:58,295 --> 00:50:00,465
- After she died?
- Yes.

800
00:50:05,305 --> 00:50:06,945
You should be worrying about yourself.

801
00:50:07,575 --> 00:50:09,315
You need to have a major ritual performed.

802
00:50:11,785 --> 00:50:14,485
There's a woman clinging to your shoulder.

803
00:50:16,015 --> 00:50:17,015
A woman?

804
00:50:18,685 --> 00:50:19,685
How old?

805
00:50:20,285 --> 00:50:22,625
She died before her time.

806
00:50:22,695 --> 00:50:25,465
What are we to do
with all that resentment?

807
00:50:52,755 --> 00:50:54,885
What did you think of the visit today?

808
00:50:55,525 --> 00:50:57,895
The way I feel now,
I think I should visit more often.

809
00:50:58,355 --> 00:50:59,525
Now that you've set your mind to it,

810
00:50:59,925 --> 00:51:01,895
you might actually go once
for every three times you say you will.

811
00:51:02,195 --> 00:51:05,335
If you'd come with me,
I'd go three times instead of two.

812
00:51:06,735 --> 00:51:07,735
Or even four.

813
00:51:08,365 --> 00:51:10,075
I'll accompany you every time you go.

814
00:51:11,475 --> 00:51:12,575
Don't make empty promises.

815
00:51:13,145 --> 00:51:14,845
Not just anyone can afford
to make empty promises.

816
00:51:15,445 --> 00:51:18,045
- Who, then?
- Someone who can afford to?

817
00:51:20,315 --> 00:51:22,485
You always seem so busy and rushed.

818
00:51:24,115 --> 00:51:25,555
Sometimes I wonder...

819
00:51:26,385 --> 00:51:27,925
if I had a lot of bad karma
in a past life.

820
00:51:28,695 --> 00:51:30,825
- Karma, is that what you call it?
- Yes.

821
00:51:31,155 --> 00:51:32,665
Maybe I was so lazy back then...

822
00:51:33,965 --> 00:51:35,465
that I don't even have
a moment to breathe now?

823
00:51:36,895 --> 00:51:37,895
If I'm being a little dramatic.

824
00:51:40,265 --> 00:51:42,405
- Here is the ribeye cap.
- Thank you.

825
00:51:47,645 --> 00:51:50,345
What kind of hope did you have
at the orphanage?

826
00:51:51,175 --> 00:51:52,945
They say there are no hopeless situations,

827
00:51:53,485 --> 00:51:55,515
only people who have given up hope.

828
00:51:56,355 --> 00:51:57,355
Who said that?

829
00:51:57,415 --> 00:51:59,885
Shimon Peres,
the former president of Israel.

830
00:52:02,895 --> 00:52:06,095
When I couldn't find any hope,
I'd use my imagination.

831
00:52:07,425 --> 00:52:08,735
Almost all the kids...

832
00:52:09,695 --> 00:52:11,835
spend a lot of time imagining
their parents coming for them.

833
00:52:13,765 --> 00:52:16,735
But I've had my reality check,
so I don't have those dreams anymore.

834
00:52:21,175 --> 00:52:24,215
But you often see stories about
families reuniting after decades.

835
00:52:25,415 --> 00:52:28,415
That's almost always for kids
who went missing or were lost.

836
00:52:31,455 --> 00:52:33,255
If I were the one who'd abandoned
my own child,

837
00:52:34,355 --> 00:52:35,795
I couldn't bring myself to look
for them out of guilt.

838
00:52:41,965 --> 00:52:43,435
Do all reporters read a lot of books?

839
00:52:44,735 --> 00:52:47,205
I think the senior editors read a ton.

840
00:52:47,665 --> 00:52:49,675
I just pile them up,
but never get around to reading them.

841
00:52:50,605 --> 00:52:53,575
In college, I was too busy working
part-time jobs to read as much as I liked.

842
00:52:54,105 --> 00:52:55,775
What kind of part-time jobs did you have?

843
00:52:58,145 --> 00:52:59,145
All sorts of things.

844
00:52:59,145 --> 00:53:01,085
Being an event guide paid pretty well.

845
00:53:02,985 --> 00:53:05,985
Do you know who the poorest king
in the world is?

846
00:53:09,095 --> 00:53:10,155
The one on minimum "wage."

847
00:53:13,565 --> 00:53:16,135
Do you have any life goals
left to achieve?

848
00:53:16,795 --> 00:53:18,665
I've achieved them all. So far.

849
00:53:19,235 --> 00:53:20,665
Oh, really? Already?

850
00:53:22,035 --> 00:53:23,275
You're incredible.

851
00:53:24,405 --> 00:53:26,745
Have you ever read a book
called "Laughter"?

852
00:53:27,705 --> 00:53:28,715
I don't think so.

853
00:53:29,345 --> 00:53:32,515
It says in your 20s,
you take pride in being able to love,

854
00:53:32,845 --> 00:53:35,255
and in your 30s,
you take pride in having a lot of money.

855
00:53:35,655 --> 00:53:36,655
What about your military service?

856
00:53:37,415 --> 00:53:38,985
Exempt. I have flat feet
and am the only son for four generations

857
00:53:39,325 --> 00:53:41,125
My dad served in the Vietnam Ski Unit.

858
00:53:41,655 --> 00:53:42,655
Oh, okay.

859
00:53:43,125 --> 00:53:44,125
What do you mean?

860
00:53:45,565 --> 00:53:47,095
There's no such thing
as a ski unit in Vietnam.

861
00:53:47,725 --> 00:53:48,735
It's a tropical country.

862
00:53:49,765 --> 00:53:50,795
Oh, right.

863
00:53:52,305 --> 00:53:53,435
So you have a clueless side to you.

864
00:53:54,305 --> 00:53:56,835
Actually, I'm pretty much a mess,
except when it comes to work.

865
00:53:57,475 --> 00:53:58,975
A little imperfection
helps you live longer.

866
00:53:59,905 --> 00:54:01,405
But you don't have any, do you?

867
00:54:02,275 --> 00:54:03,275
I guess I'm destined to die young, then.

868
00:54:04,415 --> 00:54:05,445
Director Shin.

869
00:54:06,945 --> 00:54:09,785
Parents have an obligation
to live a long life.

870
00:54:10,415 --> 00:54:12,655
Momo is carrying your baby.

871
00:54:15,995 --> 00:54:17,725
I see your teeth are fine, though.

872
00:54:18,195 --> 00:54:20,265
I heard neurosurgeons
get cracked molars...

873
00:54:20,395 --> 00:54:22,335
from clenching their teeth during surgery.

874
00:54:23,835 --> 00:54:25,135
It's too early in my career for that.

875
00:54:28,305 --> 00:54:31,605
I heard something too.
That it's tough for new reporters, right?

876
00:54:33,005 --> 00:54:34,105
It's incredibly tough.

877
00:54:34,445 --> 00:54:35,445
Speaking from experience?

878
00:54:36,675 --> 00:54:37,675
I'd rather not say.

879
00:54:38,275 --> 00:54:39,345
But I asked.

880
00:54:39,615 --> 00:54:40,885
What could you have to hide from me?

881
00:54:42,615 --> 00:54:44,155
It's not my own story, but...

882
00:54:46,455 --> 00:54:49,125
To be honest,
you're the one I find most intimidating.

883
00:54:50,725 --> 00:54:52,825
Well, don't be.
You can be comfortable with me.

884
00:55:02,005 --> 00:55:03,675
It's not that I don't trust you,
Director Shin.

885
00:55:05,805 --> 00:55:06,805
You can be comfortable with me.

886
00:55:15,015 --> 00:55:19,025
When we're on the police station beat,
seniors teach us to hold our own.

887
00:55:19,225 --> 00:55:20,955
They tell us not to let the detectives
push us around.

888
00:55:21,955 --> 00:55:25,195
One time, a son of some big-shot CEO
got busted for drugs,

889
00:55:25,495 --> 00:55:27,265
and he was being interrogated
in the Chief's office.

890
00:55:29,895 --> 00:55:31,765
You wrap your phone in a plastic bag
and take it in with you.

891
00:55:33,005 --> 00:55:34,005
It's that intense?

892
00:55:34,865 --> 00:55:37,705
You're in huge trouble
if you don't answer your seniors' calls.

893
00:55:38,805 --> 00:55:39,805
And if you get a scoop?

894
00:55:40,775 --> 00:55:41,775
You get a "good job."

895
00:55:43,775 --> 00:55:45,115
What about the exclusive interview
you got with me?

896
00:55:46,145 --> 00:55:48,645
That was a huge scoop.
I'll never forget it.

897
00:55:50,255 --> 00:55:52,015
Just remembering it isn't enough.

898
00:56:16,445 --> 00:56:19,745
(Messages)

899
00:56:21,815 --> 00:56:24,385
He might want to get rid of me,

900
00:56:25,625 --> 00:56:27,285
but he can't just take out the brain.

901
00:56:28,125 --> 00:56:30,025
To get rid of me, he'd have to kill Momo.

902
00:56:30,125 --> 00:56:32,265
Could he kill Momo and get away with it?

903
00:56:37,395 --> 00:56:40,705
Where should I go and have brunch today?

904
00:56:53,785 --> 00:56:55,615
If she finds out it's me and not Momo,

905
00:56:56,215 --> 00:56:58,015
I wonder how much
Geum Ba Ra will freak out.

906
00:57:01,455 --> 00:57:03,255
Who would've thought
I'd get to enjoy a life like this?

907
00:57:03,695 --> 00:57:05,355
An orphan like Kim Jin Ju.

908
00:57:11,595 --> 00:57:14,265
What if I put Ba Ra's brain in your head?

909
00:57:15,305 --> 00:57:17,375
No, wait. In Ba Ra's head...

910
00:57:17,935 --> 00:57:19,705
What if I put your brain in there?

911
00:57:21,075 --> 00:57:23,375
Woof, woof.

912
00:57:31,015 --> 00:57:32,755
Just remembering it isn't enough.

913
00:57:33,185 --> 00:57:34,785
Please tell me what it is you want.

914
00:57:38,355 --> 00:57:39,365
Momo...

915
00:57:40,025 --> 00:57:41,795
is seriously lacking in refinement
and general knowledge.

916
00:57:41,865 --> 00:57:42,865
(Humanities for Self-discovery)

917
00:57:42,995 --> 00:57:44,695
Recommend some books or something
for her to read.

918
00:57:45,365 --> 00:57:46,705
Do you know a good English tutor?

919
00:57:49,175 --> 00:57:50,275
Or you could just teach her yourself.

920
00:58:30,675 --> 00:58:35,215
(Do you know who the poorest king
in the world is?)

921
00:58:40,625 --> 00:58:42,225
(The one on minimum "wage.")

922
00:58:54,065 --> 00:58:55,205
Today, it's strawberry cake.

923
00:59:08,385 --> 00:59:09,385
Geum Ba Ra.

924
00:59:15,755 --> 00:59:16,955
Can I see you right now?

925
00:59:17,725 --> 00:59:18,725
Where?

926
00:59:19,425 --> 00:59:20,495
I'll text you the address.

927
00:59:21,825 --> 00:59:24,195
I can't bring Pickles, can I?

928
00:59:24,535 --> 00:59:27,265
- Why?
- I'm at Momo's, and he's all alone.

929
00:59:27,635 --> 00:59:28,635
Bring him.

930
00:59:36,845 --> 00:59:38,015
Can't I come too?

931
00:59:38,415 --> 00:59:41,185
I'm curious to see
how Yong Joong lives on his own,

932
00:59:41,815 --> 00:59:43,155
and we were going
to see each other again anyway.

933
00:59:44,555 --> 00:59:45,625
I'll ask him.

934
01:00:24,655 --> 01:00:27,495
Hello. I'm Jin Ju's dad.

935
01:00:27,565 --> 01:00:28,665
Kim Jin Ju.

936
01:00:30,235 --> 01:00:34,005
- Yes?
- Is there a bench nearby to talk?

937
01:00:35,435 --> 01:00:37,035
It'll only take a minute.

938
01:00:37,705 --> 01:00:38,705
What is it?

939
01:00:39,475 --> 01:00:40,775
Roll down the window a bit.

940
01:00:47,145 --> 01:00:48,515
You have pictures of my daughter,
don't you?

941
01:00:49,955 --> 01:00:51,315
You must have some, don't you?

942
01:00:55,285 --> 01:00:57,695
What's your number?
Send them to me, please.

943
01:00:58,625 --> 01:01:00,465
I need to at least look
at her picture to get by.

944
01:01:00,525 --> 01:01:02,265
I don't really like taking pictures.

945
01:01:03,265 --> 01:01:04,265
Who doesn't?

946
01:01:05,465 --> 01:01:06,465
Me.

947
01:01:07,465 --> 01:01:10,075
So, because you don't like taking them,

948
01:01:11,205 --> 01:01:12,335
you're saying you don't have any?

949
01:01:13,645 --> 01:01:14,645
That's right.

950
01:01:14,945 --> 01:01:17,915
But how could you
have never taken a single picture?

951
01:01:18,515 --> 01:01:19,585
You haven't even looked for one.

952
01:01:19,645 --> 01:01:20,845
I don't have any.

953
01:01:20,845 --> 01:01:23,055
I get so sick of it
that I rarely take personal photos.

954
01:01:24,415 --> 01:01:29,095
But my daughter was your stylist
for over three years, wasn't she?

955
01:01:29,795 --> 01:01:30,795
I suppose so.

956
01:01:33,625 --> 01:01:35,265
I deleted the few I had.

957
01:02:16,275 --> 01:02:17,275
Pickles!

958
01:02:22,275 --> 01:02:24,315
(Calls: Ba Ra)

959
01:02:28,685 --> 01:02:30,885
Why'd you take him without telling me?
You didn't even wait for me.

960
01:02:33,755 --> 01:02:36,025
(CEO Ha Yong Joong)

961
01:02:37,855 --> 01:02:39,865
(CEO Ha Yong Joong)

962
01:02:41,395 --> 01:02:42,395
What the...?

963
01:02:43,195 --> 01:02:44,895
(Humanities for Self-discovery,
Humanities Mindset)

964
01:02:54,045 --> 01:02:55,605
(Momo)

965
01:02:59,115 --> 01:03:00,115
(Momo)

966
01:03:07,485 --> 01:03:08,785
(Momo)

967
01:03:11,895 --> 01:03:13,465
(Momo)

968
01:03:18,195 --> 01:03:19,935
The person you're calling is unavailable.

969
01:03:19,935 --> 01:03:22,305
Please leave a message after the tone.

970
01:03:30,115 --> 01:03:31,675
(Momo)

971
01:03:36,055 --> 01:03:38,415
- Hello?
- I'm sorry.

972
01:03:39,155 --> 01:03:42,125
I was saving your number
and accidentally called.

973
01:03:42,695 --> 01:03:43,695
I see.

974
01:03:44,995 --> 01:03:46,065
Okay, bye.

975
01:03:46,765 --> 01:03:48,125
You sound a little down.

976
01:03:49,195 --> 01:03:50,195
Are you not feeling well?

977
01:03:51,395 --> 01:03:52,495
I'm fine.

978
01:03:54,305 --> 01:03:55,305
Okay.

979
01:03:56,705 --> 01:03:58,075
Can I see you?

980
01:03:58,905 --> 01:04:01,075
Sure. Are you home?

981
01:04:04,275 --> 01:04:05,985
- Yes.
- I'll head over now.

982
01:04:06,515 --> 01:04:08,485
Plan B isn't too far from you, right?

983
01:04:10,385 --> 01:04:11,385
Right.

984
01:04:11,755 --> 01:04:14,225
It's rush hour,
so it might take me 40 to 50 minutes.

985
01:04:19,055 --> 01:04:20,125
The map says we're here.

986
01:04:26,235 --> 01:04:27,235
I'll get out here.

987
01:05:33,105 --> 01:05:35,565
- It's raining.
- The sound woke me up.

988
01:05:35,975 --> 01:05:38,505
Gosh, it's really coming down.

989
01:05:38,775 --> 01:05:40,245
So much for the weather forecast.

990
01:05:40,605 --> 01:05:41,945
Call someone to come out and get us.

991
01:05:42,715 --> 01:05:45,515
If it wasn't for work, I'd be home
making some savory pancakes right now.

992
01:05:46,845 --> 01:05:48,515
Still, I got a huge thing
out of the way today.

993
01:06:02,695 --> 01:06:04,795
- You heading home?
- Yes.

994
01:06:07,665 --> 01:06:09,065
Hello, sir.

995
01:06:09,675 --> 01:06:10,835
She's one of Hanjun's assistants.

996
01:06:11,135 --> 01:06:12,135
Right.

997
01:06:37,035 --> 01:06:38,035
Get in.

998
01:06:39,705 --> 01:06:41,265
He's my brother, James.

999
01:06:49,675 --> 01:06:50,875
Thank you.

1000
01:06:57,885 --> 01:07:00,885
If you could just drop me off
in the alley by Hakdong Intersection...

1001
01:07:03,195 --> 01:07:05,755
- Are you two related?
- He's my older brother.

1002
01:07:06,265 --> 01:07:08,895
- But the age gap...
- Yes, it's pretty big.

1003
01:07:11,235 --> 01:07:12,235
Are you a stylist?

1004
01:07:12,835 --> 01:07:14,135
Just an assistant for now.

1005
01:07:17,135 --> 01:07:18,535
This rain came out of nowhere...

1006
01:07:20,045 --> 01:07:21,475
Which actor's styling team are you on?

1007
01:07:22,575 --> 01:07:26,585
- Hanjun's.
- I hear assistants only get an allowance.

1008
01:07:26,985 --> 01:07:29,285
Yes. I just graduated this year.

1009
01:07:30,415 --> 01:07:32,925
I heard my brother is hiring next month.

1010
01:07:33,385 --> 01:07:34,385
Really?

1011
01:07:35,085 --> 01:07:36,095
You should apply.

1012
01:07:36,925 --> 01:07:39,225
I'll work really hard, so if you could
put in a good word...

1013
01:07:49,205 --> 01:07:50,205
The car died.

1014
01:07:51,105 --> 01:07:53,245
- What?
- Hey, there's a taxi! Hurry!

1015
01:08:03,055 --> 01:08:04,755
- Thank you so much.
- Wait!

1016
01:08:07,185 --> 01:08:08,525
This is for the cab fare.

1017
01:08:10,295 --> 01:08:11,995
Quick, before someone else gets it.

1018
01:09:23,435 --> 01:09:26,305
(Doctor Shin)

1019
01:09:26,435 --> 01:09:28,405
Have you ever met Kim Jin Ju?

1020
01:09:29,975 --> 01:09:31,775
He had a killer body.

1021
01:09:31,835 --> 01:09:33,945
I wonder if our dinner tonight
will become a fond memory too.

1022
01:09:34,005 --> 01:09:36,315
He's way more down-to-earth
than Director Shin.

1023
01:09:36,375 --> 01:09:38,145
And I am so ready.

1024
01:09:38,345 --> 01:09:39,615
I'm Jin Ju's father.

1025
01:09:39,885 --> 01:09:40,985
Hello.

1026
01:09:41,245 --> 01:09:42,545
I'd like to meet with you.

1027
01:09:42,885 --> 01:09:43,985
I'm sorry?

1028
01:09:43,985 --> 01:09:45,015
I said I want to meet.

1029
01:09:45,085 --> 01:09:46,385
Who's texting you this late?

1030
01:09:46,855 --> 01:09:51,225
We're all hoping you and Director Shin
get back together.

1031
01:09:51,655 --> 01:09:53,265
He deserves someone better than me.

1032
01:09:53,825 --> 01:09:56,495
Could you call the ER and ask
for the doctor on duty?

1033
01:09:56,565 --> 01:09:57,595
I'm on my way.

1034
01:09:57,665 --> 01:09:58,695
Do you really...

1035
01:09:59,235 --> 01:10:00,965
want to come here?

1036
01:10:01,735 --> 01:10:03,775
You can have all the dogs you want,

1037
01:10:03,775 --> 01:10:06,275
and we can live here, together.

1038
01:10:06,875 --> 01:10:07,905
It's cliché,

1039
01:10:08,705 --> 01:10:09,745
but I'm proposing.

1040
01:10:11,575 --> 01:10:13,585
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
